  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Only few reports exist on long-term survival after minimally invasive liver surgery (MILS for
      colorectal liver metastases. No data are available assessing prognostic factors in the era of
      current modern treatment strategies. The aim of the current study is to analyze the long-term
      oncologic outcome after MILS for metastases from colorectal cancer and determine prognostic
      indicators.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
